{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 15:52:10.630901", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nSummary\n- Anomaly detected: End-user hosts are losing their IP configuration and default route shortly after boot, resulting in “Network is unreachable” for any off-link destination. \n- Fault localization: Central DHCP server (dhcp_server, 10.200.0.8).\n- Root cause: DHCP service is down on the central DHCP server while lease timers are set extremely short (default 30s, max 60s). As leases expire and cannot be renewed, hosts drop their IPv4 address and routing.\n\nKey Findings and Evidence\n\n1) End hosts have no IP address or routing\n- host_1_1_1_1 and host_2_1_1_1:\n  - No IPv4 on eth0; no routes:\n    - host_1_1_1_1 ip_addr/ip_route: eth0 UP, but no inet; ip_route empty.\n    - host_2_1_1_1 ip_addr/ip_route: eth0 UP, but no inet; ip_route empty.\n  - DNS configured to 10.200.0.2 (resolv.conf) but unreachable due to no IP.\n  - Any ping from these hosts to dns_server/load_balancer/web servers: “ping: connect: Network is unreachable”.\n  - curl http://web99.local and http://web0.local: immediate zero-duration failures (no network stack connectivity).\n\n2) DHCP server is not running; leases are very short\n- On dhcp_server (10.200.0.8):\n  - isc-dhcp-server.service: Active: inactive (dead).\n  - dhcpd.conf:\n    - default-lease-time 30; max-lease-time 60;\n    - Subnets defined for 10.1.1.0/24, 10.1.2.0/24, 10.2.1.0/24, 10.2.2.0/24 with 10.200.0.2 as DNS and appropriate gateways.\n  - dhcpd.leases shows recent active leases for many hosts, including:\n    - host_1_1_1_1 leased 10.1.1.12\n    - host_2_1_1_1 leased 10.2.1.13\n    - ...others in all access VLANs.\n  - With the server down and 30–60s lease times, clients rapidly lose their addresses when renewal fails.\n\n3) DHCP relay agents are present and appear operational\n- router_dist_1_1 and router_dist_2_1:\n  - ps shows dhcrelay running: “dhcrelay -i br0 -i eth0 10.200.0.8”\n  - systemctl reports “inactive (dead)” due to use of SysV init script, but the processes are active by command line observation.\n- This indicates DHCP relay path likely OK; the upstream server process is the failure point.\n\n4) Wider network (routing and server farm) appears healthy when hosts have IPs\n- Initial reachability snapshot (earlier in session) showed 0% packet loss and normal RTTs between many subnets and server farm nodes (dns_server, load_balancer, web_server_0..3).\n- This suggests OSPF underlay and server-access routing are in-place and functional.\n- Current inability to reach services from end hosts is consistent with loss of client IP configuration, not core routing failure.\n\nImpact Assessment\n- Scope: All access subnets relying on the central DHCP server are affected. As leases expire (30–60s), hosts become deconfigured and unable to reach DNS or any web services.\n- Symptoms: “Network is unreachable” from hosts, empty ip route, no IPv4 on interfaces, application failures to resolve/reach web99.local or webX.local.\n\nRoot Cause\n- Primary: DHCP service (isc-dhcp-server) on dhcp_server is not running.\n- Contributing factor: Excessively short DHCP lease timers (30–60 seconds) greatly accelerate the onset and recurrence of client outages when renewals fail.\n\nNon-issues/Normal\n- DHCP relays on distribution routers are running and pointing to 10.200.0.8.\n- Server farm interfaces and OSPF fabric appear normal based on earlier network-wide reachability.\n- DNS server is correctly referenced by clients (10.200.0.2), but unreachable due to lack of client IPs.\n\nNotes\n- The earlier network-wide reachability tests showed healthy connectivity; subsequent host-level checks indicate leases have likely expired since then, which reconciles the discrepancy.\n- No mitigations are proposed in this report per request.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 15905, "output_tokens": 4110, "total_tokens": 20015, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 14336}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3136}}}
